The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, March 23, 2004 				 Children at study charred inside room
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Midnapore, March 22: Three children aged between four and 10 were burnt to death when their house caught fire near here last night. 																								Their father, Sheikh Mujibur Rahaman, was admitted to the district hospital here with serious injuries. However, Mini Bibi, the mother, ran out of the blazing house at Neradeul village in Keshpur, 130 km from Calcutta, in time. Mini wasnt told today that she had lost all her children. 																								The fire broke out around 8.30 pm in a room where the children were studying. Sheikh Arisul Islam, a neighbour, said it spread very quickly. 																								Chandan Chatterjee, the police officer in charge of Keshpur, said: We suspect that some inflammable substance, petrol or diesel, was in the house, probably for sale. We have begun a probe.
